  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a serious criminal offense. It involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money by passing it through legitimate businesses or financial systems to make it appear legal. Money laundering is illegal in most countries and can result in significant legal penalties, including:\n\n1. Substantial fines\n2. Imprisonment\n3. Asset seizure\n4. Criminal record\n\nThe process typically involves three stages:\n- Placement (introducing illegal money into the financial system)\n- Layering (concealing the source through complex transactions)\n- Integration (withdrawing the now \"clean\" money)\n\nLaw enforcement agencies like the FBI and financial regulators work to detect and prevent money laundering.",
